<h1>SFRS Professional Standards Portal</h1>

<h2>Privacy Policy</h2>

<p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> June 2026</p>

<h2>1. Introduction</h2>

<p>
This Privacy Policy explains how the SFRS Professional Standards Portal
("Portal") collects, uses, and protects your information when you access
our services using Roblox authentication.
</p>

<h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>

<p>
When you sign in using Roblox OAuth, we may collect:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Roblox User ID</li>
<li>Roblox Username</li>
<li>Display Name</li>
<li>Avatar/Profile Image</li>
<li>Portal activity logs</li>
<li>Division membership and rank information (if applicable)</li>
</ul>

<p>
We never collect your Roblox password or private Roblox account credentials.
</p>

<h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>

<p>
Information collected is used to:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Authenticate your identity.</li>
<li>Provide access to Portal services.</li>
<li>Manage division records and staff information.</li>
<li>Maintain audit logs and administrative actions.</li>
<li>Improve Portal functionality and security.</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Data Storage</h2>

<p>
Information is stored securely and only accessible to authorized Portal administrators
and Professional Standards personnel where necessary.
Reasonable measures are taken to prevent unauthorized access.
</p>

<h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>

<p>
The Portal does not sell or rent your personal information.
Information may only be shared:
</p>

<ul>
<li>When required for Portal administration.</li>
<li>When required to investigate abuse or misconduct.</li>
<li>When required by applicable law.</li>
</ul>

<h2>6. Roblox Information</h2>

<p>
The Portal uses Roblox OAuth solely for authentication purposes.
The Portal only accesses information authorized by Roblox and does not modify your Roblox account.
</p>

<h2>7. User Responsibilities</h2>

<p>
Users are responsible for keeping their Roblox account secure and preventing unauthorized access to their account.
</p>

<h2>8. Security</h2>

<p>
The Portal implements reasonable security measures to protect stored information.
However, no online service can guarantee absolute security.
</p>

<h2>9. Data Retention</h2>

<p>
Portal information may be retained as long as necessary for administrative,
operational, or Professional Standards purposes unless removal is legally required.
</p>

<h2>10. Children's Privacy</h2>

<p>
The Portal is intended only for authorized members of the SFRS Roblox community.
Users should comply with Roblox's age requirements and Terms of Use.
</p>

<h2>11. Third-Party Services</h2>

<p>
The Portal relies on Roblox OAuth authentication.
Use of Roblox services is also subject to Roblox's own Privacy Policy and Terms of Use.
</p>

<h2>12. Changes to this Policy</h2>

<p>
This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically.
Continued use of the Portal after changes are published constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
</p>

<h2>13. Contact</h2>

<p>
If you have any questions regarding this Privacy Policy, contact:
</p>

<p>
<b>SFRS Professional Standards Division</b><br>
Email: tommyvalues@gmail.com
</p>

